Adds_Aqueduct Ameretat_Status_Paralysis_: Deadened nerves are sometimes preventing the execution of actions.

Adds_Aqueduct Ameretat_Status_Silence_De: A stifling magic is preventing casts.

ContentDesc_Die Unterstadt von Sil'dih: An extensive warren of tunnels and waterways stretches beneath the barren lands of Thanalan, but none come now to marvel at this remnant of fallen Sil'dih. Its memories lie undisturbed, festering silently in the dark and the damp. Yet not for much longer. You have come at the personal behest of Nanamo Ul Namo, and together will you throw open the gate to the desert nation's troubled past.
Instancecontenttextdata_34000_Text: DrAw YoUr WeApOn Of ChOiCe, AnD fAcE mE fAiR aNd SqUaRe!
Instancecontenttextdata_34001_Text: Who built this oversized mammet!? And why, oh why does it have those Amalj'aa limbs!?
Instancecontenttextdata_34002_Text: How is this fair!? It has an entire bank of artillery at its command!
Instancecontenttextdata_34003_Text: ThE iMpOsSiBlE cHoIcE... wIlL yOu TaStE sTeEl, Or WiThEr In FlAmE?
Instancecontenttextdata_34004_Text: ThE dEvIoUs SwItCh... A cLeVeR wArRiOr FoOlS tHe FoE!
Instancecontenttextdata_34005_Text: Its arms! They switched sides! What a dirty trick...
Instancecontenttextdata_34006_Text: I am vigilance unceasing... A final death unto the zombie horde!
Instancecontenttextdata_34007_Text: Zombie horde? Could this warrior have endured since the Thorne Dynasty...? But that was centuries ago!
Instancecontenttextdata_34008_Text: My wards will incinerate your undead flesh!
Instancecontenttextdata_34013_Text: Winds carry you to fiery doom!
Instancecontenttextdata_34014_Text: The flame will have its fuel!
Instancecontenttextdata_34015_Text: And still you shamble on! How hot must the fires burn to undo your foul animation!?
Instancecontenttextdata_34016_Text: My heart weeps that we must fell such a fierce ally of Ul'dah...
Instancecontenttextdata_34017_Text: Nald preserve me from creepers and crawlers. Pray clear the path, <Split([ObjectParameter(1)], ,1)/>.
Instancecontenttextdata_34018_Text: What do they feed on down here? Each other? And why must it smell so positively putrid?
Instancecontenttextdata_34020_Text: Even empty of pests, this place is a dank, mold-ridden nightmare. How long has it lain untended?
Instancecontenttextdata_34021_Text: Ugh! Pfbt! Pfbt! Thome of id fell in by bouth... Is adventuring always this disgusting!?
Instancecontenttextdata_34022_Text: I should rather not traverse a fungal bridge, but I suppose if we hurry across...
Instancecontenttextdata_34023_Text: The decay is especially bad in this section. I fear the fungal growth is all which keeps it from collapsing.
Instancecontenttextdata_34024_Text: Gah! You see!? Even the water is some ghastly shade of...wait. Is that ceruleum?
Instancecontenttextdata_34025_Text: If you can best a hecatoncheir so handily, then it certainly bodes well for the remainder of our expedition!
Instancecontenttextdata_34026_Text: To think that such a cavernous hollow yawns directly beneath Ul'dah!
Instancecontenttextdata_34027_Text: Raising one of these lifts should provide us passage across. Assuming, of course, that the winch yet functions...
Instancecontenttextdata_34028_Text: Interesting. The lift appears of Ul'dahn design, albeit an old one, but everything else screams “Amalj'aa.”
Instancecontenttextdata_34029_Text: Yes, most definitely Amalj'aa construction. Fortifications built for war, rather than habitation, I would say.
Instancecontenttextdata_34030_Text: Could this camp be from the time of the zombie purge? Was Father hoping I would see this one day...?
Instancecontenttextdata_34031_Text: Did you know that Ul'dahn and Amalj'aa once fought side by side? 'Tis not common knowledge.
Instancecontenttextdata_34032_Text: A door of solid iron─and no sign my key will open it. Do you see any handy levers or the like...?
Instancecontenttextdata_34034_Text: Who is speaking!? Well, I've not come this far to let a door turn me away. Break it down!
Instancecontenttextdata_34035_Text: Impressive! 'Tis akin to having my own personal battering ram!
Instancecontenttextdata_34036_Text: Disembodied voices, dimly lit staircases... It has the feel of a haunted crypt.
Instancecontenttextdata_34038_Text: A tragic end to a valiant warrior. He at least seemed unaware of his...affliction.
Instancecontenttextdata_34039_Text: Still, I must wonder how long this fallen hero slumbered here in cursed undeath. Trapped alone in this forgotten tomb...
Instancecontenttextdata_34040_Text: Though we worship different gods, I shall offer up a prayer for his peaceful repose all the same.
Instancecontenttextdata_34042_Text: We've uncovered much and more─plenty enough to occupy my thoughts for the time being. You have my thanks!
Instancecontenttextdata_34043_Text: Impressive! A lifetime of adventure teaches one more than just battlecraft, I see.
Instancecontenttextdata_34044_Text: 'Tis so stately and subdued in here... I am reminded of Erralig's Burial Chamber.
Instancecontenttextdata_34046_Text: A tragic end to a valiant warrior. He at least seemed unaware of his...affliction.
Instancecontenttextdata_34047_Text: And yet so abhorrent was the zombie curse, even a hero of his obvious stature was sealed behind an iron door.
Instancecontenttextdata_34048_Text: If only that powder had never been concocted... Heavy do I feel the burden of my ancestors' sins this day.
Instancecontenttextdata_34050_Text: We've uncovered much and more─plenty enough to occupy my thoughts for the time being. You have my thanks!
Instancecontenttextdata_34051_Text: Nay, this rot cannot be allowed to continue. The tunnels need reinforcement, not to mention a thorough cleaning...
Instancecontenttextdata_34055_Text: Interesting. The lift appears of Ul'dahn design, albeit an old one, but everything else screams “Amalj'aa.”
Instancecontenttextdata_34056_Text: Yes, most definitely Amalj'aa construction. Fortifications built for war, rather than habitation, I would say.
Instancecontenttextdata_34057_Text: Drakes! Just like the ones the Amalj'aa tame! Is it me, or are some of these creatures awfully large...?
Instancecontenttextdata_34058_Text: You've triggered some spell of opening! I wonder why they chose to conceal this passage...
Instancecontenttextdata_34059_Text: Oh, I see! This must be where they stored their ritual materials.
Instancecontenttextdata_34060_Text: These are precious relics, every one. Think you they might be blessed or enchanted in some fashion?
Instancecontenttextdata_34061_Text: 'Tis so stately and subdued in here... I am reminded of Erralig's Burial Chamber.
Instancecontenttextdata_34063_Text: A tragic end to a valiant warrior. He at least seemed unaware of his...affliction.
Instancecontenttextdata_34064_Text: What cruel irony that a hero of the zombie purge would become the very thing he sought to vanquish.
Instancecontenttextdata_34068_Text: We've uncovered much and more─plenty enough to occupy my thoughts for the time being. You have my thanks!
Instancecontenttextdata_34070_Text: And in mere moments, the way is clear! Hardly an inconvenience for our mighty champion.
Instancecontenttextdata_34071_Text: Surely you do not expect me to cross that rickety thing! Slowly, then...and no rocking the bridge!
Instancecontenttextdata_34072_Text: I specifically requested no rocking, bouncing, or jouncing! Gods above, I was almost pitched over the side...
Instancecontenttextdata_34073_Text: That gate looks awfully heavy. Let us try the handle, and hope these gears and chains do most of the lifting.
Instancecontenttextdata_34074_Text: Oh, it opened! I worried it may have rusted shut.
Instancecontenttextdata_34075_Text: The size of your opponent matters not, it seems! A reassuring thought as we delve further into the unknown!
Instancecontenttextdata_34076_Text: I am put in mind of mine own chambers, secret passageways and all. I wonder...
Instancecontenttextdata_34077_Text: Of course, this is the Sil'dihn royal palace! Look at this banner by the door here...
Instancecontenttextdata_34079_Text: Ah...I've seen such contrivances before. We must balance the scales ere we can proceed.
Instancecontenttextdata_34080_Text: Simply a matter of selecting the correct weights! Surely you recognize one or two of these symbols, yes?
Instancecontenttextdata_34082_Text: That gap is rather wide... Barring some unlikely acrobatics on my part, I am afraid we are at an impasse.
Instancecontenttextdata_34083_Text: Oh, but what of these levers? Their position seems highly suggestive of their relation to yon yawning pit.
Instancecontenttextdata_34084_Text: Heavens forfend... Am I to trust in this wind to carry me over!?
Instancecontenttextdata_34085_Text: How undignified! I shall be seeking out an alternate route for the return trip!
Instancecontenttextdata_34087_Text: I would not have believed anyone could topple that silver-skinned brute had I not seen it with mine own eyes!
Instancecontenttextdata_34088_Text: Thinking on it now, all these defenses were likely put in place to ensure an escape route for the royal family.
Instancecontenttextdata_34093_Text: Gracious! Would they haul the boulder up the ramp every time...? Still, I must say it makes for a stable bridge!
Instancecontenttextdata_34095_Text: I would not have believed anyone could topple that silver-skinned brute had I not seen it with mine own eyes!
Instancecontenttextdata_34096_Text: Judging by the sentinels we've encountered, 'tis clear Sil'dih's military was a force to be reckoned with.
Instancecontenttextdata_34101_Text: Oh, it opened! I worried it may have rusted shut.
Instancecontenttextdata_34102_Text: The size of your opponent matters not, it seems! A reassuring thought as we delve further into the unknown!
Instancecontenttextdata_34103_Text: We've wandered into some antique dining hall. A rich setting, indeed; one might even say “palatial.”
Instancecontenttextdata_34104_Text: Of course, this is the Sil'dihn royal palace! Look at this banner by the door here...
Instancecontenttextdata_34105_Text: Aha! That lit up the teleporter! Come along─nothing ventured, nothing gained.
Instancecontenttextdata_34106_Text: The royal treasury! A puzzle solved leading to riches untold... Just like in the stories!
Instancecontenttextdata_34107_Text: But look at these scattered coins... Has a burglar broken in before us, perchance?
Instancecontenttextdata_34109_Text: The door is open, but not so the way. Mayhap salvation lies with Nald or Thal...?
Instancecontenttextdata_34110_Text: The barrier fades! 'Twould seem your prayers were answered.
Instancecontenttextdata_34112_Text: I would not have believed anyone could topple that silver-skinned brute had I not seen it with mine own eyes!
Instancecontenttextdata_34113_Text: A dreadful sentry and a dead end chamber... I suspect this was a trap for overly ambitious thieves.
Instancecontenttextdata_34118_Text: Oho! 'Twould seem your prayers were answered.
Instancecontenttextdata_34120_Text: I would not have believed anyone could topple that silver-skinned brute had I not seen it with mine own eyes!
Instancecontenttextdata_34121_Text: There are no other exits that I can spy... I suspect this chamber was a dead end for cornering thieves.
Instancecontenttextdata_34127_Text: A storage room for ceremonial objects suggests a ceremonial chamber is nearby...
Instancecontenttextdata_34128_Text: Ah... An Amalj'aa coffin, if I am not mistaken.
Instancecontenttextdata_34130_Text: You are performing the funerary rites? Then I should light the incense, and say a prayer for the fallen.
Instancecontenttextdata_34131_Text: Another secret passage!? This place certainly is full of surprises.
Instancecontenttextdata_34134_Text: Ul'dahn and Amalj'aa banners, hanging side by side... What have we stumbled into this time?
Instancecontenttextdata_34135_Text: This book appears to be a catalog of some kind. Oh! These items are all proof of the past alliance!
Instancecontenttextdata_34136_Text: And what is this wedged in its pages...? “May the reader of this letter be our darling Nanamo.”
Instancecontenttextdata_34137_Text: If this message is for me, then why leave it here!? My parents had such faith that I would find it...
Instancecontenttextdata_34138_Text: Nay...'tis the vault itself they wished for me to discover. And these priceless truths preserved within.
Instancecontenttextdata_34139_Text: Come, let us return to Ul'dah, where I can thank you properly for your most invaluable escort!
Instancecontenttextdata_34141_Text: Three more gates...? 'Twould seem we have a choice to make.
Instancecontenttextdata_34143_Text: Oh, we've picked the same gate! That settles that, then!
Instancecontenttextdata_34144_Text: Hm, why that one...? Very well. The adventurer knows best!
Instancecontenttextdata_34146_Text: These creatures look distinctly unfriendly. If you would be so kind...?
Instancecontenttextdata_34147_Text: Barely a test of your mettle, I see. Well done!
Instancecontenttextdata_34148_Text: Some manner of rodent? Surely even I can best a couple of mice...
Instancecontenttextdata_34149_Text: Gah! Not mice, not mice, definitely not mice!
Instancecontenttextdata_34150_Text: Strange to think these giant pipes lie unseen, just yalms beneath the streets of Ul'dah...
Instancecontenttextdata_34151_Text: That culvert at the back is positively clogged. Would more water flush out the mud, I wonder?
Instancecontenttextdata_34152_Text: Oh, that redirected the water flow! 'Tis the first I've seen such a mechanism at work!
Instancecontenttextdata_34153_Text: Where do you suppose that water went to...?
Instancecontenttextdata_34155_Text: These waterways are in dire need of maintenance. I must arrange something with the palace custodians.
Instancecontenttextdata_34158_Text: Strange. Its aether feels awfully, well, familiar, if you would pardon the pun.
Instancecontenttextdata_34159_Text: You see that bubble around its puff? That must be how it channels its cleaning magicks!
Instancecontenttextdata_34161_Text: That grape-embossed helm... 'Tis the mark of a Sil'dihn-forged gladiator!
Instancecontenttextdata_34165_Text: Have a care! Those gusts will blow you clear into the air!
Instancecontenttextdata_34166_Text: Watch out! They had more boulders up there!
Instancecontenttextdata_34170_Text: A hecatoncheir!? Why would it make its lair in this muddy pit?
Instancecontenttextdata_34171_Text: Why would a hecatoncheir be down here!? It seems disinclined to let us pass peacefully...
Instancecontenttextdata_34172_Text: What is that noise? Something coming down the drainage pipes?
Instancecontenttextdata_34173_Text: Ugh, the reek of sewage is overpowering! Does this hecatoncheir have no sense of smell!?
Instancecontenttextdata_34174_Text: That bluish film atop the water is ceruleum! But that hardly explains the hecatoncheir in the room...
Instancecontenttextdata_34175_Text: Watch your footing! 'Tis coming up through the floor!
Instancecontenttextdata_34176_Text: Is that a hecatoncheir!? And what are those in the walls? Windmills?
Instancecontenttextdata_34177_Text: Is that a hecatoncheir!? And those rollers... Some form of conveyance?
Instancecontenttextdata_34179_Text: Is he playing games...? Mind the barrel tops─there must be a reason for those markings.
Instancecontenttextdata_34204_Text: And victory is yours! I am blessed to keep company with such a formidable ally.
Instancecontenttextdata_34207_Text: Ah, that breeze feels wonderful after the stuffy closeness of the tunnels.
Instancecontenttextdata_34208_Text: Bother. My key was not made to open this gate. ...Hm? It says here, “Two eyes are needed to see.”
Instancecontenttextdata_34209_Text: Two eyes... Some manner of riddle, do you suppose?
Instancecontenttextdata_34210_Text: Oh! This was no simple pattern on the floor! It was a teleportation portal!
Instancecontenttextdata_34211_Text: Let's see where it leads, shall we?
Instancecontenttextdata_34212_Text: Golems! And blocking the path we mean to take, no less.
Instancecontenttextdata_34213_Text: Who would have abandoned their cleaning gear in here?
Instancecontenttextdata_34214_Text: ...And why do I feel I've seen these particular brushes before?
Instancecontenttextdata_34215_Text: 'Twould seem you discovered the custodian's closet...
Instancecontenttextdata_34216_Text: Have you heard the Ul'dahn folktale of the magicked ewer?
Instancecontenttextdata_34217_Text: 'Tis said that it could scoop up any amount of water at once, and was locked away after it drained an entire oasis.
Instancecontenttextdata_34219_Text: That final burst of aether confirmed my suspicions: 'twas definitely Mother who created the silkie.
Instancecontenttextdata_34221_Text: Such a beautiful garden! Not the sort of place one expects to find at the end of a grimy tunnel.
Instancecontenttextdata_34223_Text: These things belonged to Mother and Father!
Instancecontenttextdata_34224_Text: This must have been their quiet little retreat; the familiar put in place to protect it.
Instancecontenttextdata_34225_Text: I should have liked to come here with them, but 'tis comforting to feel the echo of their presence, nonetheless.
Instancecontenttextdata_34226_Text: <sigh> Whilst I should like to linger still, I fear Papashan will soon note my absence. Let us be away.
Instancecontenttextdata_34227_Text: This rug, too, seems a relatively recent addition. See how the stone beneath it is cracked and worn?
Instancecontenttextdata_34228_Text: 'Tis doubtful some thief had a sudden fit of decorating...but we shall leave it for now. Other mysteries abound.
Instancecontenttextdata_34229_Text: Talk of jugs behind barred doors reminded me of the legend, is all. Shall we continue on?
Instancecontenttextdata_34231_Text: The silkie's aether... It had the exact same feel as Mother's.
Instancecontenttextdata_34233_Text: Such a beautiful garden! Not the sort of place one expects to find at the end of a grimy tunnel.
Instancecontenttextdata_34238_Text: <sigh> Whilst I should like to linger still, I fear Papashan will soon note my absence. Let us be away.
Instancecontenttextdata_34239_Text: And victory is yours! I am blessed to keep company with such a formidable ally.
Instancecontenttextdata_34241_Text: All this greenery makes for a nice change. And look: have you ever seen fruits like these!?
Instancecontenttextdata_34242_Text: Aha! That seemed to do the trick...though the riddle itself yet confounds me. A puzzle for another day.
Instancecontenttextdata_34246_Text: The silkie's aether... It had the exact same feel as Mother's.
Instancecontenttextdata_34247_Text: My, what a picturesque scene! See how the sunlight falls upon the flowers just so.
Instancecontenttextdata_34248_Text: I wonder, could this be the sanctuary of which my parents spoke?
Instancecontenttextdata_34249_Text: They told me of a private place to which they would slip away; a haven from the bustle of palace life.
Instancecontenttextdata_34250_Text: Mother always called it their “secret garden.”
Instancecontenttextdata_34251_Text: And assuming that giant mouse─the silkie─was hers, then I imagine it was here to protect their special spot.
Instancecontenttextdata_34252_Text: Finding this place must have been the reason Father gave me the key. One reason, at least.
Instancecontenttextdata_34253_Text: <sigh> Whilst I should like to linger still, I fear Papashan will soon note my absence. Let us be away.
Instancecontenttextdata_34255_Text: The silkie's aether... It had the exact same feel as Mother's.
Instancecontenttextdata_34256_Text: My, what a beautiful garden! See how the sunlight falls upon the flowers just so.
Instancecontenttextdata_34257_Text: Mother must have wanted to protect this place. Why else set the silkie to guard it?
Instancecontenttextdata_34258_Text: I imagine her coming here with Father, to simply sit and enjoy the tranquility.
Instancecontenttextdata_34260_Text: <sigh> Whilst I should like to linger still, I fear Papashan will soon note my absence. Let us be away.
Instancecontenttextdata_34263_Text: Ware the deluge of water! You will be washed away for sure!
Instancecontenttextdata_34264_Text: All those puffs in a row... You had best keep on your toes!
Instancecontenttextdata_34266_Text: The puffs are lathered with soap now... I fear they mean business!
Npcyell_14163_Text: What a stench... I shall have to burn these clothes.
Npcyell_14164_Text: Careful! That big one looks nasty!
Npcyell_14166_Text: Is there no end to this foul menagerie!?
Npcyell_14167_Text: Best give that a wide berth...
Npcyell_14168_Text: 'Tis all in such a sorry state of disrepair.
Npcyell_14170_Text: After you. I've an aversion to needles.
Npcyell_14173_Text: Is this a lair or a holding pen?
Npcyell_14175_Text: Who knows what we shall find!
Npcyell_14176_Text: Have we reached a dead end?
Npcyell_14183_Text: We must be deep in the heart of the aqueducts...
Npcyell_14184_Text: Not that way. The debris is impassable.
Npcyell_14185_Text: What did I do!? Did we trip the defenses!?
Npcyell_14186_Text: The sentinels still guard their post...
Npcyell_14188_Text: Aaah! W-Was that not the right answer!?
Npcyell_14195_Text: We must be deep in the heart of the aqueducts...
Npcyell_14196_Text: Not that way. The debris is impassable.
Npcyell_14197_Text: Snakes!? Why must it be snakes...?
Npcyell_14198_Text: Well, right or wrong, the door lies open!
Npcyell_14199_Text: Quite an expansive abode. Shall we try upstairs?
Npcyell_14203_Text: This has the look of a stage or arena...
Npcyell_14205_Text: This has the look of a stage or arena...
Npcyell_14206_Text: Let us take a peek, shall we?
Npcyell_14207_Text: Now to see what it was guarding...
Npcyell_14209_Text: I find myself drawn to this one...
Npcyell_14211_Text: We can walk through this pipe, I think.
Npcyell_14220_Text: They'll not let us pass without a fight...
Npcyell_14224_Text: Our respite was short-lived, I see.
Npcyell_14225_Text: The fruit must have drawn them here...
Npcyell_14228_Text: Still more? Every ilm of this place is infested!
